## 1. Definitions

**"Software"** means the ThreatRecall API source code, object code, API
specifications (including OpenAPI schemas), documentation, configuration
files, Docker images, deployment scripts, SDK libraries, governance
templates, test suites, and any other materials distributed in the repository
located at https://github.com/rolandpg/threatrecall-api, including all
updates, modifications, and derivative works authored by the Licensor.

**"Service"** means any hosted instance of the Software operated by the
Licensor or an authorized party that provides ThreatRecall functionality over
a network via HTTP API endpoints.

**"Licensor"** means Patrick George Roland II.

**"You"** means the individual or legal entity exercising permissions granted
by a separate Commercial Agreement with the Licensor. In the absence of such
an agreement, no permissions are granted beyond those in Section 3.

**"Commercial Agreement"** means a written and executed contract between You
and the Licensor that expressly grants rights to access the Service or use,
deploy, or distribute the Software, including but not limited to SaaS
subscription agreements, pilot agreements, evaluation agreements, enterprise
license agreements, or API access agreements.

**"API Key"** means a unique authentication credential issued by the Licensor
to You under a Commercial Agreement, granting access to the Service within
the scope and limits defined by that agreement.

